Strings Library
 This is a simple library of string functions which make simple
 string operations less tedious in solidity.
 Please be aware these functions can be quite gas heavy so use them only when
 necessary not to clog the blockchain with expensive transactions.
 @author Abraham Udele <hello@abrahamudele.com>

Strings Library
 This is a simple library of string functions which make simple
 string operations less tedious in solidity.
 Please be aware these functions can be quite gas heavy so use them only when
 necessary not to clog the blockchain with expensive transactions.
 @author Abraham Udele <hello@abrahamudele.com>

params._base: When being used for a data type this is the extended object               otherwise this is the string base to compare against
params._value: The string the base is being compared to

returns._0: bool Simply notates if the two string have an equivalent

params._base: When being used for a data type this is the extended object              otherwise this is the string which will be the concatenated              prefix
params._value: The value to be the concatenated suffix

returns._0: string The resulting string from combinging the base and value

compare(string,string).notice: Compares the characters of two strings, to ensure that they have an identical footprint

concat(string,string).notice: Concat (Has high gas cost) Appends two strings together and returns a new value

reverse(string).notice: Return a string in a reversed format
